This paper deals with dialogue state tracking, which is a subfield of natural language processing and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models for dialogue state tracking, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of crowdsourcing for data annotation, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the correction of errors in the original dataset, which falls under the category of data cleaning and preparation (cs.SD).
